bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>xærz zærond ūs kʼæʒ læʒæǵy ʽncæjtty kærty dwaræj ærbaxyzt</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>совсем старая женщина, опираясь на кривую палку, вошла в дворовые ворота</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a very old woman entered through the yard gate leaning on a crooked cane</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_F."/><biblScope>1957 I 28</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æncojad wælærvty</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>мир на небесах</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>peace in heaven</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Лука"/><biblScope>%i19%i 38</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*hаm-č(у)ānа</w></mentioned> от %ič(у)ā-%i ‘покоиться’ и пр., см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncajyn"/>. По форме %iæncoj%i относится к <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncajyn"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncad"/>, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fælloj"/> ‘труд’ к <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fællajyn"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fællad"/> ˈусталыйˈ или <ref type="xr" target="#entry_koj"/> ‘молва’ к <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kad"/> ‘слава’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*ančān- (ʼnčʼn-)</w><gloss><q>прекращение</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘успокоение’. Ср. также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncon"/>. %n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>5 сл.</biblScope></bibl></etym><etym xml:lang="en">Goes back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*hаm-č(у)ānа</w></mentioned> from %ič(у)ā%i ˈto reposeˈ etc., cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncajyn"/>. As for its structure, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncoj"/> is related to <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncajyn"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncad"/> in the same way as <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fælloj"/> ‘work’ relates to <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fællajyn"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fællad"/> ‘tired’ or <ref type="xr" target="#entry_koj"/> ‘rumour’ relates to <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kad"/> ‘fame’. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*ančān- (ʼnčʼn-)</w><gloss><q>cessation, calm(ing)</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncon"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>5 ff.</biblScope></bibl></etym></entry>